Xi's speech | Military parade | Commemoration Ceremony | Patriotic songs
Elsewhere around China, people have also been paying their respects to the nation’s heroes.
A monument at the Xifengkou Gate of the Great Wall in North China’s Hebei Province stands in memory of a battle in 1933 against Japanese invaders. The Chinese army killed over three thousand Japanese troops, and claimed a victory in one chapter of a long war.
And in Northwest China’s Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, soldiers and locals held a memorial ceremony for the 168 PLA soldiers who gave their lives to build a road linking northern and southern Xinjiang.
Moving south to the Tibet Autonomous Region, people laid flowers in front of the monument to the heroes who made contributions to the development of the region.
People pay their respects to the nation’s heroes in Tibet, China.
Soldiers held a memorial ceremony to pay their respects to the nation’s heroes in Xinjiang, China.



